# Mailmap — normalise commit attribution displayed by GitHub and `git shortlog`.
#
# Format: <canonical name> <canonical email> <legacy name> <legacy email>
# Reference: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitmailmap
#
# GitHub respects this file when rendering the Contributors sidebar,
# commit author/co-author chips, and `Insights → Contributors`. It does
# not modify the underlying git objects — it's a display-only routing
# layer applied at view time.

# Re-attribute AI co-author trailers in legacy commits to the project
# owner. Affects 4 historical commits with `Co-Authored-By: Claude …`
# trailers (still reachable via `refs/pull/1/head`).
requie <tarique.smith@gmail.com> Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
requie <tarique.smith@gmail.com> Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
# Catch-all for any other name attached to the anthropic noreply email.
requie <tarique.smith@gmail.com> <noreply@anthropic.com>

# Collapse author-name variants for the same email into the canonical
# username so GitHub doesn't show two "people" for the same person.
requie <tarique.smith@gmail.com> Tarique Smith <tarique.smith@gmail.com>
requie <tarique.smith@gmail.com> Tarique smith <tarique.smith@gmail.com>
